Of course, you can refer to these figures individually. For example,
\begin{verbatim}
  {\bf Fig. \ref{fig:5}} shows that the results given in
  {\bf Figs. \ref{fig:1}} and {\bf \ref{fig:2}} can be $\cdots$.
\end{verbatim}
will result in

\vspace{2em}
\fbox{\begin{minipage}{.75\textwidth}
{\bf Fig. \ref{fig:5}} shows that the results given in
{\bf Figs. \ref{fig:1}} and {\bf \ref{fig:2}} can be $\cdots$.
\end{minipage}}

\vspace{2em}
